Description: Fragment of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Oval handle. Diamond-shaped stamp with branch symbol. Clay near fine light red-brown; cream slip.
Curator's comments: Drawn by Petrie (Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p.173, 33). Name Theumnastos. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, MGR 1127.34?
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1061)
